Keep aliased tools/list responses coherent after registry mutation.

Virtual aliases are supported by upstream and may carry different filters.
Cache keys must therefore retain both virtual and resolved ids, and
invalidating a canonical registry must evict every alias that resolves to it.
The dedicated Nix launcher uses separate direct and unified registries, but
retains this general cache-correctness fix for other Anvil configurations.

The ERT regression decodes JSON-RPC responses and covers canonical tool
register/unregister cache invalidation plus tools, resources, templates,
resource reads, and tool calls through a virtual server id.

